
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-tiloca-6tisch-robust-scheduling-02.txt'>
    <title>"Robust Scheduling against Selective Jamming in 6TiSCH Networks", Marco Tiloca, Simon Duquennoy, Gianluca Dini</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-tiloca-6tisch-robust-scheduling-02.txt</link>
    <description>This document defines a method to generate robust TSCH schedules in a 6TiSCH (IPv6 over the TSCH mode of IEEE 802.15.4-2015) network, so as to protect network nodes against selective jamming attack.  Network nodes independently compute the new schedule at each slotframe, by altering the one originally available from 6top or alternative protocols, while preserving a consistent and collision-free communication pattern.  This method can be added on top of the minimal security framework for 6TiSCH.</description>
    <dc:date>2019-06-10T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
